In C, if you know there are more than one variable, and there are all kind of relative, you can use array.
In C, if you want to have one variable, but that can store multiple values, you use which called arrays.
Array is the list of values that can be all the same type in a variable of the same name.

int scores[3];
scores[0] = 72;
